ABOUT:
Sheath Blight is caused by Rhizoctonia solani. It infects the lower leaf sheath, spreads rapidly, and can cause major yield loss.

SYMPTOMS:
Elliptical lesions on leaf sheath
White fluffy fungal growth
Lodging of plants in severe cases
Leaf rot and drying

PREVENTION:
Reduce plant density to allow airflow
Avoid excessive nitrogen application
Use resistant varieties if available
Apply fungicides like Validamycin
